reviews.review_text: A friend brought me here , usually just walk past by this restaurant. I enjoyed the braised beef so much and I was fascinated about the stuffed chicken wings! I must try next time and their coffee with bear!

This place is fantastic! They have chicken wings stuffed with rice and other proteins, which tastes surprisingly really good! We got some take out food from them, and still tasted amazing after being in the microwave. I highly recommend their curry chicken omurice :)
Very good combination of fried rice inside a chicken wing. Both are very well done, great combination! Dont forget to try their HK Milk tea with a cute bear inside!

Michi Crafted Kitchen, signature fried chicken wings, stuffed with sticky rice. I ordered scrambled eggs and prawn combo.  Especially when surrounding with those nostalgia decor of Hong Kong,that s just super satisfying and comforting. Recommended dishes

Food was very good and the milk tea bear drink was adorable and tasted very much like Hongkong styled milk tea as well! The atmosphere was nice. My girl friend and I had a great time catching up here.

Wow so delicious I loved everything honestly havent been this completely satisfied from a restaurant in a while! We tried the Curry chicken omelet rice and the aburi pork rib bowl the Curry was rich and delicious the chicken tender and tasty. The pork ribs were also extremely tender and cooked perfectly the pork also came with a little lemon and a citrus salad on the rice so in combination with the Curry it was perfect. I also tried the bear black tea and it was a little bitter for my taste but the bear was super cute   I also enjoyed that they served barley tea with the meal    afterwards we were given orange slices as well   I cant wait to come back and try out more of the menu
Such a fun menu and atmosphere. Dishes are creative and delicious. As Hong Kong style cafes go, its on the pricier side, but definitely worth a try for a unique dining experience

Delicious and creative! I tried every type of stuff chicken wing, and my favourites were: sticky rice with sausage and egg, and the lamb rice. Least favourite was the corn and cheese, I found that the corn really overpowered the taste of the chicken. Its a really cozy space with a nice ambience. I would definitely recommend this place and would definitely come again.
Small n cozy place with great lunch combos!! Their omeltte rice with curry chicken is a must try!!. Delicious
Great idea of putting feature rice into grilled chicken wings. Clean and warm environment. Great service. Would come back for sure.
I enjoyed the chicken wings and rice dishes

Went to the restaurant few days ago. The young lady in purple hair is very friendly(forgot the name). The food is good with best service. My son spilled the water on the table and on the floor. She cleaned up with smile face and with patient. Thanks a lot!

The best tasting stuffed wing out of all the flavors is the spicy one. Others are not as good. Second best is the sticky rice one. I always go back for the spicy fried rice wings. They are so good! That s the only thing I keep ordering again and again from this restaurant.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Hilary,Thank you for taking the time to write us a review.

reviews.review_text: The food was really good, great presentation even for take out and the care with the packaging is a very nice touch. I loved that the order came with orange slices to compliment the meal (got the BBQ pork rice) . Very friendly staff, the place looks really clean and nice decor. Im definitely going back there and trying the other dishes as well.
Tasty!! My family and I really liked unique chicken wings that are well seasoned with tasty rice options. Really love the nostalgic decor in here which also makes for a great casual ambiance.

I love the michi, especially the sticky rice one! It can be seen as expensive but there is so much labor involved in making one, I see it no different than ordering sushi. I tried the squid ink pasta recently for delivery and they were super accommodating in offer eggs instead of shrimp due to my allergy. Would definitely recommend and will be back myself!
Their food is super good! I love their omelet rice and Chicken wings, especially the cheesy one! I definitely will try it agin!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Lorna, thank you for your review.

reviews.review_text: This was my first time eating a stuffed boneless wing and man was it delicious! The sticky rice was perfect and the flavour was great (not too salt either). Would definitely recommend and come back.

I went to the newly opened downtown Robson location. I liked the stuffed chicken wings, the jumbo shrimp, and the milk tea with bear. The value was good for what you get. The highlight is the 70s style diner vibe.
Cozy place with HK comfort food. Strong a/c and kids utensils are definitely a plus. Good food and good service overall. More people should know about this place
The michis (stuffed chicken wings with rice) are quite good and unique! Very tasty. My personal favourite is the omelette rice with beef stew! Yum.
Server was so kind and gave us great service and attention to detail. Came by to check on us and offered oranges :] would recommend the spicy stuff chicken. :]
Ive never tried their stuffed chicken so I cant say anything about that, but the mains (the spaghetti and the omelette rice) were really good
Old HongKong style decor w very nice stuffed chicken. Lovely drink AND food. 10/10 recommend.
We ordered Lemongrass spaghetti and Omlette rice with stewed beef, its very delicious!
The curry Fish Ball and Spicy Crawfish Michi were among my favourites from what I had
Really enjoyed the spicy michis. Disappointed they took the kimchi michi off the menu, hope they will bring it back. The pork and rice was also good.
So tasty and innovative! The stuffed wings are my favourite, especially the sticky rice one.
So many unique items at this restaurant so i had to try. Thoroughly enjoyed everything and will definitely be back!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Melissa, This does not sound like the experience we want our customers to have. Please contact us at michiyvr@gmail.com to discuss further. Thank you

reviews.review_text: First time trying Michi Craft Kitchen, food was great, definitely will come back again.
Food was fantastic! The wings are so delicious and staff are awesome! Id definitely come back
Great restaurant, made us feel like home. Great wings and customer service from Leslie.
Omg love this place. Food is amazing bal$e.
Good place to catch up with friends. Food is good and served promptly
Bro that Jumbo Turkey Wing is like 5 times bigger than the regular one
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi, Thank you so much for the kind review! Take care and we will see you soon.

reviews.review_text: Ppl should understand that Its the process and labour that worth the money.
Nice place, will go again!
Great service
Original and delicious!
Fingerlickingly good
Super tasty!!!!
super delicious
Super delicious! Ive been eating here since the store opened, and the ladys attitude is super good:) My mother misses this bite every time
The chicken wings are great and delicious~ The beef brisket omelette rice is also great~~
This is too delicious! Good deal!
I often order this place for delivery delicious every time Recommend beef brisket rice with omelet Hope to have more menu options in the future
I went to eat at night, the service of the young lady is very good, and the food is also very good
Very good, the chicken rice wings are the best in Greater Vancouver, highly recommended!
The car is not easy to park, but the rest is perfect
Delicious and caring
Delicious ~ service attitude is also very good

My friend really loves the omourice here. I came to give it a chance. It was not bad but I felt like the flavors was something I could curate in my own kitchen. Although presentation of the dishes were very well done.

A nice spot for a meal by Boundary and Kingsway. The space is kind of small but we were able to get a table for 6 no problem. The milk tea bear is super overpriced but it s so cute! The stuffed chicken is very unique and tasty - they re super filling. My friends also got the curry and tomato omelette rice and said they were delicious too!

Ordered two double michi combos so we could try as many flavours as possible, all the flavours were great! Originally thought prices were high for a single chicken wing but with all the stuffing ingredients we left feeling like the price was actually very reasonable

I passed by and was wondering what stuffed wings were. I was not dissapointed. I got the cumin chicken and the pork sausage with salted egg yolk. Both were absolutely delicious. The Thai tea is great for when you need some adorable moments in your day. Their prices are reasonable. Their omurice was not only tasty but looked really good too ( i would have gotten a better shot but my spouse was eager to tuck in :p)

I would come back for more!!!! Not only the decor strung a special chord in my childhood memory but the food is pretty good!!! We ordered the omelette rice, squid ink pasta and wings to share amongst 3 ppl. The milk tea bears are expensive at $5.99 (compared to other milk tea prices in the market) but the presentation is so cute!!! I got the cheesy corn stuffed wing and omg I wish I can make this at home   we came at a good time when they opened so the place wasnt packed at all.

We had a good time here. I love the old Chinese film posters--super nostalgic. The milk tea is so cute and comes with a little bear shaped milk tea cube. I think people need to realize how much work it is to debone a chicken wing. This is their signature dish and its stuffed with different flavours to try and its quite filling. Parking: Street parking
Nice place, not too much space, but the dishes are tasty. I ordered tomato omelette with beef and combo chicken wings Drinks were passion fruit lemonade and hot milk bear tea

We ordered the original, cheesy corn and cumin lamb fried rice. They were good. Also I ordered the green sauce spaghetti with lemongrass chicken it was basically pesto sauce with heavy cream... a little bit too salty for my taste but hey you never know it might be perfect for you. Cant wait to try spicy fried rice and curry fried rice. Well definitely come back here. Plenty of parking or paid parking very close to the Telus building in Boundary and Kingsway

First time trying the stuffed wings at this place. I tried 3 flavors and personally enjoyed the original one the most.  Note I used one of the many food delivery services. It s interesting not all the delivery fees are equal on each one. Good packaging and presentation.

Decent food with a lot of choices. It s not just stuffed chicken wings here, there are also pastas and rice bowls! We pretty much ordered most of the menu and everything tasted great (albeit the lamb chicken wing being too salty and where s the lamb?). One star docked because of the BAD customer service. It was a quiet Friday evening when we went but the waitress basically hid behind the counter and didn t even refill our water once. It also took ages to get our bill and they had no other table.
Loved the concept of chicken wings stuffed with fried rice and was not disappointed at all. I will definitely come back to try other flavours
Authentic Hong Kong style restaurant friendly staff little tight on parking would come back again
Delicious and enjoyable experience.  Fun staff, cute waitress.  Insanely powerful A/C had a chill down my spine throughout my meal.  Overall good!
The chicken wing with corn and cheese stuffing taste not bad. The restaurant gave three slices of orange as a small gift.
Stuffed wings were huge! I really liked the curry. Wish the decor was more like the one on Robson and had their cute drinks.
Great service. Cute cozy place for a meal. We really enjoyed their delicious pesto spaghetti and also their braised pork belly on rice.
First time trying this place and I throughly enjoyed the stuffed wings especially the curry rice one.
More than chicken rings.  Lots of HK movie posters

Thought it was light snacks but ended up getting so full. Its more comfort food and the price is a bit steep but the food is very tasty. The store has really nice interior decorations going for a vintage Hong kong street style. Fun place to have a light meal and hang out with friends
Well priced combos, unique flavours on their rice stuffed wings.
Tasty quick meal option, will come back again.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the great review !  We look forward to having you in again!
